b> Constraint Satisfaction Problem(CSPs)
    It is a special subset of state-space problems. Instead of finding a path of actions, the goal is to find a state that satisfies all constraints.
    example: Map coloring, sudoku



BFS:
uses Queue
Based on FIFO
Traversers along immediate neighbours


heuristic cost: Estimated distance from current node to destination or goal.

Actual cost g(n): Distance between current node and its neighbouring node.